<seg id=1> Indonesia Police Summoned a Journalist to Interrogation for His Report of A Woman of Chinese Origin Being Raped in May </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (FNA news from Jakarta)The Journalists Protection Commitee which is for the preservation of freedom of the Press showed their astonishment that the Indonesia Police summoned a reporter for his report of a woman of Chinese origin being raped in riot of May. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Journalists Protection Commitee with an agency in New York said that the reporter Gunavan working for the magazing "Jakarta - Jakarta" was summoned to the police headquarters for interrogation on Thursday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Commitee said that Gunavan quoted the words of a woman being raped in one of his news reports in July </seg>
<seg id=5> The New York Times also used the words of the same victim in its report on June, 10. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Commitee said in the letter to Indonesia President Harbibi that the summons issued was the beginning of the police' action of accusation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> They expressed their "serious concerns about the negative influence of application of such laws on the freedom of speech". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The Commitee was referring to the pressure on the government from the Indonesia Islamic Community to arrest Gunavan according to the 156 clause of the criminal laws, </seg>
<seg id=9> which forbids defamation to religious groups. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> The International Independent Journalists Union also protested against the police summons of Gunavan </seg>
<seg id=11> by saying that it would set a precedent for reducing the wider range of freedom of the media since the end of the office of former President Soeharto. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Otherwise, the Journalists Protection Commitee urged President Harbibi to stop the action against Gunavan and asked all sides to resolve the disputes on the civil court </seg>
<seg id=13> It also called upon people for "utmost efforts in the elimination of the defamation clauses in Indonesia Criminal Laws". </seg>
</p>
